transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop quote management tutorial series.

In our last video we talked about how the customer requests a quote from the front store, how admin takes action on the received quote and how the customer approves the quote and finally converts the quote to an order.
If everything falls into place in today's video, we will see how a quote can be placed from the admin account.

If you have received any queries regarding product pricing and details over call, e-mail, WhatsApp or through other platforms, you can send them the quotation from the admin panel by asking for more details.
This will also give them the option to see details in their account and place the order.
So let's get started.
Go to the admin panel, navigate to Quote Management and then click on View Quotes.
On the Quote listing page, you can see all the quotes received from the customers.
To add a quote, click on the Add New Quote button from the top right corner.
Add the form by filling in the quote title, first name, e-mail address, last name and number of the customer.
Enable the Notify button to send a notification of this quote to the customer.
Now it is time to add product details as per the details received from the customer.
You need to define if the product is the existing one or if it is a custom requirement.
For now let's select existing.
Select a product from the list.
As soon as you select the product, the additional details will be fulfilled in the below fields.
You can change the selection as per customer requirements.
Enter multiple quantities.
Add the information in the Additional Details field, upload any sample artwork they have shared with you, and finally add the SKU of the selected product specification.
If they have more than one product combined in the same quotation, then you can add that with the Save and add another Product button or else you can click the Save and Continue button.
As you click on the save and continue, the quotation will be placed on behalf of the customer.
Now comes your part of adding the pricing details and other stuff and then sharing it with your customer.
The steps and flow of the quotation are the same as those we have discussed in the Quote Management Introduction video.
The customer can check the details from the My Quotes section of the My Account menu.
After login.
To check the details, they need to click on the View Details or Review Update Quotation button.
They can enter their comments, select the quantity they want to proceed with, and then approve or reject the quote.
When they choose to proceed and click on the approved quote, they will be redirected to the quote design upload page or shopping cart page.
Based on the settings with the shipping and payment details specified, the customer can place the order.
That's it.
You have successfully placed an offline quote from the admin panel on behalf of your customer.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshocom.
Thanks for tuning in.
